text: #Chelsea (7/7): His entry into the football business comes as a surprise. In recent years, Wyss has devoted himself to philanthropy: With his Wyss foundation, he is committed to preserving the landscape and protecting species.

author: Nicola Imfeld
text: #Chelsea (6/7): Wyss has been a football fan since childhood. As a young boy, he used to play in his spare time in the Weissenstein district. As he got older he lost sight of the game a bit due to academic and professional commitments.

author: Nicola Imfeld
text: #Chelsea (5/7): In 1977, he bought into the orthopedics company Synthes, which turned out to be a goldmine. In 2012, Wyss sold Synthes to U.S. pharmaceutical giant Johnson & Johnson. Today, his estimated net worth is $5,1 billion.

author: Nicola Imfeld
text: #Chelsea (4/7): Wyss took his first steps in a small three-room apartment in Bern's Weissenstein district. He studied civil engineering at the ETH Zurich and later at the renowned Harvard Business School.

author: Nicola Imfeld
text: #Chelsea (3/7): According to the @nytimes, Wyss would have played a not inconsiderable role in the election of U.S. President Joe Biden to the White House. Wyss rarely speaks out publicly and was often described as a Â«phantomÂ».

author: Nicola Imfeld
text: #Chelsea (2/7): Wyss is the most influential Swiss in the world. He has a great political influence and is regarded in America as a puppet master. An article about him appeared in the @nytimes a year ago: Â«Swiss billionaire quietly becomes an influential force among DemocratsÂ».

author: Absolute Chelsea
text:
Frank Lampard:

"That's not the only part of it this weekend [facing #Chelsea]. My thoughts are with Everton, my only thought is preparing the team to win the game. That's what every person at Chelsea will expect me to do. I'll focus on that."

author: Absolute Chelsea
text:
Frank Lampard on whether facing #Chelsea means more to him:

"I don't think so. Chelsea is always a big part of my life - 13 years of my career as a player, 18 months as a manager. Nobody will expect me to feel differently about the club.
